  "text": "It has been stated that porosity will be beneficial in the process manufacturing of bone implants. Reza [CITATION_1] has shown that there is no significant change in mechanical properties from foam material after the immersion process in Hanks solution [CITATION_2] . One of the most promising fabrication methods for creating porous materials is the space holder method. This method utilizes ceramic or polymer to be sintered, and it will produce porosity in the desired shape. Bram et al. have succeeded produce porous materials using carbamide, as a raw material space holder (foam agent) of titanium and stainless steel [CITATION_3] . Gulsoy and German succeed to produce 17-5PH stainless steel metal foam using carbamide. They found the porosity that resulted from the process is related with the number of carbamides in the alloy [CITATION_4] . Bekoz, and E. Oktay (2012) successfully made a spherical foamed structure in Fe-1.5Mo% materials using carbamide [CITATION_5] . The compressive stress increased significantly compared with the irregular porosity.",
